        "formula": "Let beta = 1.0. For i in [0, 32768) and j in [0, 32768): diff_{i,j} = predictions[i,j] - targets[i,j]; loss_{i,j} = if |diff_{i,j}| < beta then 0.5 * diff_{i,j}^2 / beta else |diff_{i,j}| - 0.5 * beta. Output L = (1 / (32768 * 32768)) * sum_{i=0}^{32767} sum_{j=0}^{32767} loss_{i,j}.",
        "boundary_treatment": "The condition |diff| < beta uses the quadratic branch, otherwise (including equality) uses the linear branch. Input shapes are assumed identical; no broadcasting is needed. The input is non-empty under given get_inputs(), thus empty-tensor NaN is not considered.",
